"Botany, derived from the Greek botanē (meaning pasture, herb, grass, or fodder), is the scientific study of plants, encompassing their structure (anatomy and morphology), biochemical processes (physiology), classification (taxonomy), ecology, distribution, diseases, and interactions with the environment.
