Overall Assessment
Demand is robust and growing for integrative, problem-solving research addressing real-world problems, especially where kingdoms intersect (e.g., rhizosphere microbiomes, fungal symbioses, algal biofuels, bacterial nitrogen fixation). Pure descriptive botany or narrow taxonomy faces headwinds due to training declines, but this creates opportunities for those entering the field.
